[2] Cholera - Angola (Luanda)
Date: Mon, 20 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.andnetwork.com/app?service=direct/1/Home/
$StorySummary$0.$DirectLink$1&sp=l19310>

6 people have died in a week in Boavista ward, Ingombota district,
due to a cholera outbreak diagnosed by health authorities of the
Angolan capital, Luanda.
The fact was announced on Sun, 19 Feb 2006, at a press conference
organised by the Government of Luanda Province in partnership with
representatives of the Health Ministry and of WHO.
According to the Luanda's Deputy Governor for social sphere,
Francisca do Espirito Santo, 32 cases have been detected, from which
half of the deaths were of children below 5 years of age.
Angolan Health Deputy Minister, Jose Van-Dunem, declared that health
units will be set up in all districts, adding that medical and
medicine assistance will be free.
--
