[3] Cholera - Uganda (Koboko District)
Date: Mon, 20 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: New Vision [edited]
<http://www.newvision.co.ug/D/8/16/482881>

The cholera outbreak in southern Sudan has attacked at least 24
people in Koboko district in the last 2 weeks.
The district director of health services, Dr. Alfred Driwale, on Fri,
17 Feb 2006 said the first patient came from Sudan on 3 Feb 2006, but
died 3 hours later. He said they received 2 other cases, one of whom
went to Maracha county in Arua district but was managed at home and
improved. "The outbreak started on 10 Feb 2006 and since then 24
people have been infected," Driwale said.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
