[6] Diarrhea - South Africa (Northwest Province)
Date: Sun, 19 Feb 2006
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: IOL, South Africa. 19 Feb 2006 [edited]
<http://www.iol.co.za/index.php?set_id=1&click_id=&art_id=qw1140364081148B262>

At least 1000 people have been infected in an outbreak of diarrhea in
Bloemhof, North West health department said on Sun, 19 Feb 2006. The
toll had risen from 400 on Sunday, said spokesperson Barba
Gaoganediwe. He could not confirm reports that 3 children had died.
"We have not yet received any reports of the deaths...we are checking
with the Lekwa Tamane municipality," he said.
All indications were that the residents became ill on Fri, 17 Feb
2006, after drinking contaminated water from dams and rivers.
Water samples taken in Bloemhof and nearby Vryburg were being tested
for a strain of diarrhea-causing amoebae.
--
